{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.5",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 5,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 5",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 5 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.5.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:1",
      "text": "“Call now; is there any one who will answer you? To which of the holy ones will you turn?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.5.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:2",
      "text": "Surely vexation kills the fool, and jealousy slays the simple.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.5.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:3",
      "text": "I have seen the fool taking root, but suddenly I cursed his dwelling.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.5.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:4",
      "text": "His sons are far from safety, they are crushed in the gate, and there is no one to deliver them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.5.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:5",
      "text": "His harvest the hungry eat, and he takes it even out of thorns; and the thirsty pant after his wealth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.5.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:6",
      "text": "For affliction does not come from the dust, nor does trouble sprout from the ground;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.5.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:7",
      "text": "but man is born to trouble as the sparks fly upward.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.5.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:8",
      "text": "“As for me, I would seek God, and to God would I commit my cause;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.5.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:9",
      "text": "who does great things and unsearchable, marvelous things without number:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.5.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:10",
      "text": "he gives rain upon the earth and sends waters upon the fields;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.5.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:11",
      "text": "he sets on high those who are lowly, and those who mourn are lifted to safety.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.5.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:12",
      "text": "He frustrates the devices of the crafty, so that their hands achieve no success.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.5.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:13",
      "text": "He takes the wise in their own craftiness; and the schemes of the wily are brought to a quick end.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.5.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:14",
      "text": "They meet with darkness in the daytime, and grope at noonday as in the night.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.5.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:15",
      "text": "But he saves the fatherless from their mouth, the needy from the hand of the mighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.5.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:16",
      "text": "So the poor have hope, and injustice shuts her mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.5.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:17",
      "text": "“Behold, happy is the man whom God reproves; therefore despise not the chastening of the Almighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.5.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:18",
      "text": "For he wounds, but he binds up; he smites, but his hands heal.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.5.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:19",
      "text": "He will deliver you from six troubles; in seven there shall no evil touch you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.5.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:20",
      "text": "In famine he will redeem you from death, and in war from the power of the sword.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.5.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:21",
      "text": "You shall be hid from the scourge of the tongue, and shall not fear destruction when it comes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.5.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:22",
      "text": "At destruction and famine you shall laugh, and shall not fear the beasts of the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.5.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:23",
      "text": "For you shall be in league with the stones of the field, and the beasts of the field shall be at peace with you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.5.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:24",
      "text": "You shall know that your tent is safe, and you shall inspect your fold and miss nothing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.5.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:25",
      "text": "You shall know also that your descendants shall be many, and your offspring as the grass of the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.5.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:26",
      "text": "You shall come to your grave in ripe old age, as a shock of grain comes up to the threshing floor in its season.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.5.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:27",
      "text": "Lo, this we have searched out; it is true. Hear, and know it for your good.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
